Non-Commercial Clause Addendum

Preamble
The GNU Affero General Public License is designed to ensure that users have the freedom to share and change all versions of a program--to make sure it remains free software for all its users. This version of the AGPL includes an additional clause that restricts commercial use of the software.

TERMS AND CONDITIONS

1. Definitions
"Non-commercial" means not primarily intended for or directed towards commercial advantage or monetary compensation.

2. Basic Permissions
You may copy, distribute, and modify the software provided that the use is non-commercial and you retain all copyright and license notices. Any distribution must include a copy of this license.

3. Source Code
You must make the source code of any modifications you distribute publicly available under the terms of this license.

4. Non-Commercial Use Only
This software is licensed for non-commercial use only. Commercial use is prohibited without prior written consent from the copyright holder.

5. Distribution
Any distribution of this software or its modifications must retain this license and the non-commercial clause.

6. Remote Network Interaction
If the software is used to interact with users over a network, the source code must be made available to those users.

7. Patents
Contributors grant a patent license to users, ensuring that patents cannot be enforced against users of the software.

8. No Warranty
This software is provided "as is," without any warranty of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to the warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.

END OF TERMS AND CONDITIONS
